	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Reviewed system statistics from ~1500-1800 PST.  Everything looks completely normal, no anomalies.  Reviewed MySQL system statistics during the same time frame -- same, normal.  No excessive CPU load, memory I/O, or disk I/O was happening during that time frame.  Same goes for our network uplink.  I also reviewed periodic traceroutes we run to destinations (none in Brazil though) -- no anomalies with our co-lo provider.
<br />
<br />So, chances are what you were witnessing was the unreliability of the Internet (you're still in Brazil, right?  :-) ).  It happens.  There may have been some IP routing convergence issues, or some network links somewhere between you/us were saturated, etc...  Believe me, happens all the time (daily).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


