<br /><strong>EDIT:</strong> found the cause. It was a problem with a submarine cable. 
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://tecnoblog.net/83563/pane-infraestrutura-embratel-lentidao/">http://tecnoblog.net/83563/pane-infraes ... -lentidao/</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Translating:
<br />
<br /><em>Yesterday afternoon (28/11) detected a break in the region of Fortaleza in one of our submarine cables, responsible for fast access to sites of our U.S. servers. We do not know the cause of this occurrence, but our staff acted promptly and take corrective action to enable the contingency of our services. As a result, customers Virtua had no interruption in their services and only some users (about 20 percent) are noting that Internet access is a little slower than normal. The final repairs are being implemented and the services will be fully normalized in the day.</em>

		

